pkgmetadata.longdescription: # alembic-autogen-check[![Travis-CI](https://badgen.net/travis/4Catalyzer/alembic-autogen-check/master)](https://travis-ci.org/4Catalyzer/alembic-autogen-check)## Install```pip install alembic-autogen-check```## Usage```PYTHONPATH=. alembic-autogen-check```This assumes that an `alembic.ini` file exists in the current workingdirectory. You can explicitly pass a config file:```PYTHONPATH=. alembic-autogen-check --config path/to/alembic.ini```
